ffective data augmentation techniques and ensuring model generalization across different medical conditions.",\n\n  "[Question 4] - Why hasn\'t it been solved before?": "Previous research has primarily focused on general image-text pre-training models like CLIP, which are not tailored to the specific challenges of medical data. Existing medical image-text models often suffer from data insufficiency and lack the ability to capture subtle medical meanings. Our approach addresses these gaps by developing a specialized pre-training method for medical images and reports, incorporating semantic matching tasks, and leveraging limited available data more effectively.",\n\n  "[Question 5] - What are the key components of my approach and results?": "Our proposed methodology involves developing a specialized medical image-text pre-training model (MedCLIP) that incorporates semantic matching tasks and utilizes limited available medical datasets. We will use datasets such as CheXpert and MIMIC-CXR for training and evaluation. Key metrics include zero-shot accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score for image recognition and cross-modal retrieval tasks. Expected outcomes include improved zero-shot performance, better label efficiency for downstream classification tasks, and enhanced cross-modal retrieval capabilities compared to existing models."\n}\n```', 'continue_simulation': True, 'communications': ['In Session 7dc0239e-d8b8-4dc2-871a-37323e18781f \nFrom agent3 to agent4: Agent4, just following up to see if you have had a chance to review the proposed research idea and provide your feedback. Your insights are crucial for refining the project. Thank you!\n', 'In Session a9e2490a-efa0-4291-ac99-682e823c0554 \nFrom agent4 to agent1: I am starting the implementation of the initial components of the methodology. Here is the detailed plan: [Insert detailed plan here].\n'], 'total_milestones': 0, 'agent_kpis': {}}], 'planning_scores': [-1, -1, -1], 'communication_scores': [-1, -1, -1]